  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: \r\n  Geth\r\n  Version: 1.7.3-stable\r\n  Git Commit: 4bb3c89d44e372e6a9ab85a8be0c9345265c763a\r\n  Architecture: amd64\r\n  Protocol Versions: [63 62]\r\n  Network Id: 1\r\n  Go Version: go1.9\r\n  Operating System: windows\r\n  GOPATH=\r\n  GOROOT=c:\\go\r\n\r\nGeth version for machine with the wallet program which shouldn't be used either way: \r\n  Geth\r\n  Version: 1.7.3-stable\r\n  Git Commit: 4bb3c89d44e372e6a9ab85a8be0c9345265c763a\r\n  Architecture: amd64\r\n  Protocol Versions: [63 62]\r\n  Network Id: 1\r\n  Go Version: go1.9\r\n  Operating System: windows\r\n  GOPATH=\r\n  GOROOT=c:\\go\r\n\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAccept connections from wallet.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nssh pipe reports: channel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nSo obviously the wallet is correctly trying to connect, however, geth is NOT listening on the rpc port...\r\nThere are no networking errors from geth.\r\nHowever there is a single instance of:\r\nERROR[...] Failed to generate mapped ethash dataset epoch=1 err=\"open C:\\\\cygwin\\\\home\\\\FU\\\\AppData\\\\Ethash\\\\full-R23-290decd9548b62a8.4606018198686923411: Access is denied.\"\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n$ geth --cache=64 --networkid=435343 --datadir=\"ethereum1\" -verbosity 3 --port 30302 --rpcport 8102 --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --rpccorsdomain \"...\" --ipcdisable --bootnodes \"`cat boot.url`\" --etherbase=\"0xc8164a7b5e194509412939961f858a2f966b0007\" --minerthreads=1 --mine console 2>ethereum1.log;\r\n\r\n[from remote computer]\r\n#also tried localhost:8102\r\n$ ssh -i ....pem user@serverwithgeth.com -N -L 8102:127.0.0.1:8102\r\n$ ./Ethereum\\ Wallet.exe --rpc \"http://localhost:8102\"\r\n[... blah blah ...]\r\n[...] [ERROR] ClientBinaryManager - Sanity check failed for Geth Error: Unable to find \"1.7.2\" in Geth output\r\n[... downloading new geth binary??? unexpected behavior to say the least ...]\r\n\r\n[this is the point where I get this output from the ssh pipe from before]\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\nchannel 2: open failed: connect failed: Connection refused\r\n",
